Learning journals are a great way to differentiate activities when you are homeschooling multiple ages. I do one history or science lesson for both of my kids. And then they complete individual activities in their learning journal that are age and developmentally appropriate. I keep everything we did for that subject in the learning journal. This is a great way to show academic growth and progress throughout the course of the year. #homeschool #homeschooling #teachermom #sahm #momcontent #creatorsearchinsights

Do you include read alouds in your homeschool?  if so, try reading journaling. It is a great way to keep track of all of the books that you have read together throughout the school year. It is also a way to include story and literary elements into your read aloud time.

as an avid coffee drinker, this was a really tough pill for me to swallow. I spent years not feeling well and seeing doctors who told me it was hormonal or, my favorite, anxiety. until a few months ago my symptoms got so bad my body started to shut down. thats when I found out I had mold toxicity.  And no, it wasnt all from coffee. Environmental mold played a role. But I was also consuming so much through what I was eating and drinking, my body could no longer keep up and eliminate the toxins.  Im a big believer in if you know better, you can do better. Switching out your coffee is an easy way to do better for your body.  Thanks for coming to my TED talk.
